Japan's Fuji Bank Ltd. said Thursday group pre-tax  earnings plunged 31.7 percent from a year earlier to 68.3 billion yen (663  million dollars) in the year to March and forecast a further decline this year.
The bank said consolidated revenues were down 11.5 percent at 2,715  billion yen while net operating profit tumbled 43.5 percent to 32.9 billion  yen.
Fuji forecast a lower group profit of 65 billion yen for the current year  with revenue dropping to 2,450 billion yen and net operating profit falling to  30 billion yen.
